eraction. We propose a\nscenario where the lower mass galaxy has its SF suppressed by gas heating or\nstripping, while the higher mass galaxy has its SF enhanced, potentially by\ntidal gas turbulence and shocks. This is consistent with the seemingly\ncontradictory observations for both SF suppression and enhancement in close\npairs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 16 Jul 2015 04:49:28 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-07-17"}
