r, superradiant phase transition, the order-disorder type\nferroelectrics in the cavity electromagnetic field, the advantage of the\nsystems capable to self-organization, including the suppression of the\ntemperature influence as the decoherence factor acting on the work states of\nthe qubits (atoms, ferroelectric molecules), and also the coherent character of\nthe direct dipole-dipole interaction between qubits (in the case of\nferroelectrics), and other items.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 16 Jul 2015 15:39:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-07-30"}
